node.text:
#AD A super easy dessert with @mcvitiesofficial chocolate digestive nibbles, perfect for the festive season!

RECIPE

4 Egg Yolks 120g Caster Sugar 50g Cornflour 2 tbsp Cocoa Powder 500ml Milk 1 ½ tsp Espresso Powder or Instant Coffee Granules 1 tsp Flaky Sea Salt Homemade or shop bought brownies or chocolate cake, roughly chopped 120g McVitie’s Chocolate Digestive Nibbles 400ml Double Cream

Make the chocolate custard by whisking together the egg yolks and sugar. Add in the cornflour and cocoa powder and whisk until thickened and smooth.

Heat the milk and coffee granules in a saucepan until just before boiling. Pour a little milk into the egg mixture ad whisk briefly to combine. Continue to pour in the milk a little at a time and whisk until all the milk has been added.

Pour this back into the saucepan over a gentle heat and whisk constantly until the custard thickens and starts to bubble. Stir in the sea salt and remove from the heat. Pour the custard into a bowl, place some cling film on the surface of the custard and refrigerate until firm. Once chilled, whisk thoroughly to remove any lumps.

In a small bowl, whip the double cream to get soft peaks and set aside. Roughly chop some of the McVities Chocolate Digestive Nibbles and gently fold this into the cream. Fill a piping bag with the cream and snip off the end.

To assemble the trifles, layer the bottom of the glass with your brownies or chocolate cake. Pipe on a layer of whipped cream followed by a sprinkle of the chocolate digestive nibbles. Add a layer of the chocolate custard and a layer of brownie or cake. Top with more whipped cream and decorate the top with some more chocolate nibbles. 
#mcvitiesofficial #festivebaking

node.title: AD | Salted Chocolate & Coffee Trifles with McVitie’s

node.text:
#AD Here’s an easy festive no bake cheesecake with @mcvitiesofficial
RECIPE

250g McVitie’s Chocolate Digestive Biscuits, plus extra to decorate 100g Unsalted Butter, melted 30g Ground Almonds 250g White Chocolate 360g Cream Cheese 50g Caster Sugar Zest of 1 Orange 200ml Double Cream 2 tbsp Amaretto

To decorate: 200ml Double Cream Dried Orange Slices Fresh Rosemary Toasted Flaked Almonds

Make the base by crushing the McVitie’s Chocolate Digestives in a food processor until fine. Stir in the melted butter and ground almonds and press into the base of a lined springform tin. Chill in the fridge for 30 minutes.

Melt the white chocolate over a pan of simmering water and set aside to cool. In a large bowl whisk the cream cheese with the caster sugar until smooth. Stir in the orange zest. Pour in the cooled white chocolate and beat for 2 mins.

Whisk in the double cream followed by the amaretto and spoon onto the biscuit base. Smooth the top and let it set in the fridge for 4-6 hours or overnight.

For the topping, whip up the double cream to soft peaks and spoon on top of the cheesecake. Decorate with some crushed chocolate digestives, dried orange slices, fresh rosemary and white chocolate shavings.

node.title: AD | White Chocolate & Orange Cheesecake with McVitie’s

node.text:
#ad I’m going for a French inspired breakfast today with a plate full of silky crepes. I’ve switched things up a bit and incorporated some @cartenoireuk Classique ground coffee into the batter - such an easy addition but makes for a great fancy breakfast along with some whipped cream and chocolate sauce.
 
And if you fancy winning a hamper of French treats including some Carte Noire coffee and cafetiere, just take a picture of your own breakfast and tag @cartenoireuk and #breakfastlikethefrench
 

Ends: 4th July. Prize draw T&C’s bit.ly/3xQpZhU

node.text:
Get comfortable using herbs in your baking friends! Thyme is one of my favourites to use and it’s such a great way of adding a bit more interest to classic bakes. The recipe for this blueberry and thyme frangipane tart is online over at @guardianfeast. Enjoyyy 🌿

📸: @ritaplattsphoto 
Props @wilko_anna

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Benjamina | Recipes and Baking on June 15, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text:
Ice cream sandwich season is hereeee. ☀️I’ve gone for pistachio biscuits here and squished them together with a no churn fresh mint and cardamom ice cream. 😍 
I love a proper pepperminty ice cream(mint choc chip is my absolute fave) but using fresh mint here gives it a softer, more herbal vibe that I just love. 

Recipe is up now up on my blog, link in bio. Let me know if you give them a go! 💛

node.text: Rainy day pies. This is a pretty hearty savoury pie filled with potato and cauliflower because the weather right now in the middle of May is very rude 😫
